# Rule 2 — Coding standards

Sources: `docs/development/coding-standards.md`, `naming-conventions.md`, `phpcs.xml`, `.editorconfig`.  
Gate: `php composer.phar ci` (PHPStan → PHPCS → PHPUnit).

## PSR-12

- Follow **PSR-12** for all PHP (enforced by PHPCS).
- PHP **≥ 8.3**.
- Indentation: **tabs** for `.php` (see `.editorconfig`); one class per file.
- Braces, visibility, and import order per PSR-12; no closing `?>` tag.
- Keep lines readable; don’t fight the linter — fix what PHPCS reports.

## Strict types

- Every PHP file starts with:

```php
<?php

declare(strict_types=1);
```

- Use typed properties, parameter types, and return types.
- Prefer `mixed` only when unavoidable; narrow with PHPDoc array shapes.

## PHPDoc

- Document **public** contracts (classes, methods, interfaces).
- Use precise generics/shapes: `list<string>`, `array<string, mixed>`, `@param`, `@return`, `@throws`.
- Don’t restate the obvious (`@param string $name Name of the thing`) — document intent, units, and invariants.
- Mark deprecations with `@deprecated` + replacement.

## Naming conventions

| Kind | Convention | Example |
| ---- | ---------- | ------- |
| Namespace | `OpenMeta\<Package>\...` | `OpenMeta\Fields\Registry` |
| Class | PascalCase, noun | `FieldRegistry`, `RestKernel` |
| Interface | PascalCase + `Interface` suffix | `ContainerInterface` |
| Exception | PascalCase + `Exception` | `AuthorizationException` |
| Method / function | camelCase, verb phrase | `register()`, `make()` |
| Property / variable | camelCase | `$fieldEngine` |
| Constant | UPPER_SNAKE | `Permission::MANAGE_FIELDS` |
| Config / env keys | snake_case or dotted | `database.default` |
| WP hooks (when used) | `openmeta_*` prefix | `openmeta_ready` |

Names must be descriptive and unambiguous — no 1–2 letter identifiers in public API.

## Folder naming

```text
packages/<package>/          # lowercase package id: core, fields, wordpress
  src/                       # PSR-4 root for OpenMeta\<Package>\
    Contracts/               # or domain folders: Container/, Rest/, …
    Exceptions/
  tests/
    Unit|Integration|WordPress|Performance|Security/
  resources/                 # optional assets
  README.md
  SPEC.md
```

- Folder names under `src/` are **PascalCase** matching the sub-namespace (`Rest/`, `DragDrop/`).
- Do **not** rename packages or invent parallel trees outside this layout.
- Never move files across packages to “make imports easier.”

## File naming

- **One** public class/interface/enum per file.
- Filename = short class name + `.php` → `Container.php`, `ContainerInterface.php`.
- Tests: `*Test.php` (PHPUnit); test case bases: `*TestCase.php` (excluded from suites as today).
- No `class.inc.php` or lowercase `foo_bar.php` for classes.

## Constructor injection

- Inject collaborators via the **constructor**; promote to `private readonly` (or typed props) when possible.
- Wire graphs in **ServiceProviders** (`singleton` / `bind`) — consumers don’t `new` deep collaborator trees.
- Avoid setter injection and static service locators in domain code.
- No static mutable registries unless SPEC requires and it’s documented.

## Interfaces first

- When SPEC defines a public contract → create the **interface** before (or with) the implementation.
- Type-hint interfaces in constructors and method signatures; bind interface → concrete in the provider.
- Don’t depend on foreign package **internals** — only their public contracts / façades.
- Prefer small role interfaces over large “god” interfaces (ISP).

## Also required

- Prefer `final` classes unless extension is an explicit extension point.
- Escape output / authorize via `@openmeta/security` — not ad-hoc helpers.
- Match the existing package’s patterns before inventing a new style.
